<subSubSection id="23B9656B9B00FF959FB1F9E0FE429465" box="[151,408,1545,1572]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" type="description">
<paragraph id="6B1C36E09B00FF959FB1F9E0FE429465" blockId="14.[151,843,1510,1572]" box="[151,408,1545,1572]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
(
<figureCitation id="F3982A659B00FF959FB9F9E0FF3E9465" box="[159,228,1546,1572]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1923,1948]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06470); E−H, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06468); I−L, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (holotype 06472)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253624/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Figs 3</figureCitation>
I–L, 5M–R, 10)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="23B9656B9B00FF959FB1F9BBFC299498" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6B1C36E09B00FF959FB1F9BBFC299498" blockId="14.[151,1437,1617,2041]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis id="59D7EAF29B00FF959FB1F9BBFEC8942D" bold="true" box="[151,274,1617,1644]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Epandrial ventral lobe with apical acute projection (
<figureCitation id="F3982A659B00FF959C4EF9B8FC08942D" box="[872,978,1618,1644]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1818,1843]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,166,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[161,1425,166,1798]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hirtodrosophila nigrispina sp. nov. (A−N: holotype 06472; O−Q: paratype 06473). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, D, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral and posterior view, respectively; red arrow point at apical projection); E, cerci (ventral view); F, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); H, I, 10th sternite (anterior and dorsal view, respectively); J−L, phallic organs (ventral, ventro- lateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, sensilla of paramere (ventrolateral view); N, lateral process of aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at fine serration); O, P, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); Q, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253630/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
). Cercus ventrally with numerous black, thick spines nearly the same in size (
<figureCitation id="F3982A659B00FF959D1AF99CFD7994D1" box="[572,675,1654,1680]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1818,1843]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,166,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[161,1425,166,1798]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hirtodrosophila nigrispina sp. nov. (A−N: holotype 06472; O−Q: paratype 06473). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, D, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral and posterior view, respectively; red arrow point at apical projection); E, cerci (ventral view); F, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); H, I, 10th sternite (anterior and dorsal view, respectively); J−L, phallic organs (ventral, ventro- lateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, sensilla of paramere (ventrolateral view); N, lateral process of aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at fine serration); O, P, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); Q, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253630/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Fig. 10E</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus apically broadened, medial margin flat in ventral view, with a pair of lateral processes and medial membranous protrusion (
<figureCitation id="F3982A659B00FF959CBFF970FC3094F5" box="[921,1002,1690,1716]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1818,1843]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,166,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[161,1425,166,1798]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hirtodrosophila nigrispina sp. nov. (A−N: holotype 06472; O−Q: paratype 06473). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, D, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral and posterior view, respectively; red arrow point at apical projection); E, cerci (ventral view); F, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); H, I, 10th sternite (anterior and dorsal view, respectively); J−L, phallic organs (ventral, ventro- lateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, sensilla of paramere (ventrolateral view); N, lateral process of aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at fine serration); O, P, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); Q, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253630/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
J–L); lateral processes distally parallel with each other in ventral view, finely serrate on dorsal margin (
<figureCitation id="F3982A659B00FF959C43F954FC3D9498" box="[869,999,1726,1753]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1818,1843]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,166,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[161,1425,166,1798]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hirtodrosophila nigrispina sp. nov. (A−N: holotype 06472; O−Q: paratype 06473). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, D, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral and posterior view, respectively; red arrow point at apical projection); E, cerci (ventral view); F, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); H, I, 10th sternite (anterior and dorsal view, respectively); J−L, phallic organs (ventral, ventro- lateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, sensilla of paramere (ventrolateral view); N, lateral process of aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at fine serration); O, P, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); Q, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253630/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Fig. 10J, N</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="23B9656B9B00FF8A9FE1F90BFEAA93CA" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="130" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" type="description">
<paragraph id="6B1C36E09B00FF959FE1F90BFD0895F1" blockId="14.[151,1437,1617,2041]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis id="59D7EAF29B00FF959FE1F90BFE8B94BD" bold="true" box="[199,337,1761,1788]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Description</emphasis>
(characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName id="ACA34D639B00FF959D8BF909FCF694BD" authority="Chen &amp; Katoh &amp; Gao, 2019" authorityName="Chen &amp; Katoh &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2019" box="[685,812,1762,1788]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhangae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="59D7EAF29B00FF959D8BF909FCF694BD" box="[685,812,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">H. zhangae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="59D7EAF29B00FF959C15F908FC5694BD" bold="true" box="[819,908,1762,1788]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="42E457899B00FF959C15F908FC5694BD" box="[819,908,1762,1788]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
not repeated) (
<specimenCount id="7DA5FD699B00FF959B13F908FB9694BD" box="[1077,1100,1762,1788]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount id="7DA5FD699B00FF959B7EF909FBB694BC" box="[1112,1132,1763,1789]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). Head (
<figureCitation id="F3982A659B00FF959BE8F908FAE294BC" box="[1230,1336,1762,1789]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1923,1948]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06470); E−H, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06468); I−L, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (holotype 06472)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253624/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
Figs 
<date id="1F1D10209B00FF959A20F908FAC594BD" box="[1286,1311,1762,1788]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">3I</date>
, J
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F3982A659B00FF959A62F90BFA8B94BD" box="[1348,1361,1761,1788]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1609,1634]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,849,1589]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,849,1589]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 5. Head (anterior view), postocciput (posterior view), cibarium (dorsal and lateral view), and prementum (ventral and lateral view). A−F, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06474); G−L, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06471); M−R, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (paratype 06473)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415691" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415691/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">5</figureCitation>
M–R): Frontal vitta brown. Fronto-orbital plate dark brown, anteriorly paler. Ocellar setae inserted slightly inside triangle made by ocelli. Face and facial carina brown, ventrally darker. Gena yellowish brown, anteriorly darker. First flagellomere dark grayish brown. Supracervical setae ca. 10 per side; postocular setae 23–26 per side. Clypeus brown to dark brown. Palpus pale grayish yellow, with one apical and 1–2 subapical, prominent setae. Cibarium with ca. seven medial and 23–25 posterior sensilla per side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B1C36E09B00FF959FE1F851FB4295B8" blockId="14.[151,1437,1617,2041]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
Legs (
<figureCitation id="F3982A659B00FF959E2BF850FE819595" box="[269,347,1978,2004]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1923,1948]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06470); E−H, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06468); I−L, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (holotype 06472)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253624/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
Fig. 
<date id="1F1D10209B00FF959E67F850FE819595" box="[321,347,1978,2004]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">3I</date>
</figureCitation>
): Foreleg 1st tarsomere shorter than total length of four succeeding tarsomeres. Mid- and hindleg 1st tarsomeres slightly shorter than or as long as total length of four succeeding tarsomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B1C36E09B01FF949FE1FF73FBF892F2" blockId="15.[151,1437,153,539]" box="[199,1058,153,179]" pageId="15" pageNumber="128">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="F3982A659B01FF949E63FF73FE6E92F2" box="[325,436,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1923,1948]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[232,1355,166,1904]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left lateral habitus, head and thorax (dorsal view), wing (left ventral or right dorsal view), and abdomen (dorsal view). A−D, H. zhangae sp. nov. (holotype 06470); E−H, H. zouae sp. nov. (holotype 06468); I−L, H. nigrispina sp. nov. (holotype 06472)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253624/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="128">Fig. 3I, L</figureCitation>
): Caudal bands medially often narrowed or interrupted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B1C36E09B01FF949FE1FF57FE4F93CA" blockId="15.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="128">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation id="F3982A659B01FF949EA0FF57FE0E9296" box="[390,468,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1818,1843]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,166,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[161,1425,166,1798]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hirtodrosophila nigrispina sp. nov. (A−N: holotype 06472; O−Q: paratype 06473). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, D, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral and posterior view, respectively; red arrow point at apical projection); E, cerci (ventral view); F, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); H, I, 10th sternite (anterior and dorsal view, respectively); J−L, phallic organs (ventral, ventro- lateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, sensilla of paramere (ventrolateral view); N, lateral process of aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at fine serration); O, P, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); Q, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253630/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="128">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
A–N): Epandrium with ca. 28 long setae per side. Cercus with 37–41 long setae, ventral ones thicker. Surstylus ventrally tapered and vent posteriad, with upper row of ca. six prensisetae, and lower row of ca. seven prensisetae; inner surface with ca. 18 long setae, anterior ones longer and thinner; anterior margin with ca. four short setulae. Tenth sternite anteromedially concaved, somewhat heart-shaped in ventral view. Paramere with ca. five minute sensilla along apical to dorsosubapical margin. Aedeagal apodeme straight, thin, much shorter than and fused to aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B1C36E09B01FF949FE1FE7FFDDF905A" blockId="15.[151,1437,153,539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="128">
Female terminalia (
<figureCitation id="F3982A659B01FF949E8FFE7FFE2793EE" box="[425,509,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1818,1843]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,166,1798]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[161,1425,166,1798]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hirtodrosophila nigrispina sp. nov. (A−N: holotype 06472; O−Q: paratype 06473). A, B, periphallic organs (posterior and posterolateral view, respectively); C, D, ventral lobe of epandrium (lateral and posterior view, respectively; red arrow point at apical projection); E, cerci (ventral view); F, dorsal part of surstylus (posterolateral view); G, inner surface of surstylus (posterolateral view); H, I, 10th sternite (anterior and dorsal view, respectively); J−L, phallic organs (ventral, ventro- lateral, and lateral view, respectively); M, sensilla of paramere (ventrolateral view); N, lateral process of aedeagus (lateral view; red arrows point at fine serration); O, P, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); Q, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253630/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="128">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
O–Q): Tergite VIII grayish brown to dark grayish brown, pubescent dorsally to caudolaterally. Oviscapt valve distally somewhat quadrate in lateral view, with ca. four lateral and ca. 16 marginal, peg-like ovisensilla. Spermathecal capsule slightly broader than long, with introvert about 4/5 height of capsule; introvert only scarcely wrinkled.
</paragraph>
